WEBVTT

00:00.674 --> 00:01.515
Good afternoon.

00:01.716 --> 00:02.216
Good morning.

00:02.276 --> 00:03.939
Good to see everybody on this summer day.

00:03.999 --> 00:07.184
Hot and humid.

00:07.344 --> 00:08.546
I am glad you're here.

00:08.826 --> 00:15.977
And as they said earlier, you know, it's summertime and there's a lot of cool things just came out of the children's camp.

00:16.298 --> 00:21.205
We've got student camp coming up and then we have the great American baptism party.

00:21.266 --> 00:23.088
I hope you'll be a part of that.

00:23.289 --> 00:24.210
It's going to be

00:24.290 --> 00:27.134
A really, really exciting summer.

00:27.555 --> 00:30.939
And today we're starting a brand new series called Subscribe.

00:31.220 --> 00:33.964
How many of you watch YouTube at least once a week?

00:34.084 --> 00:34.825
Let me see your hand.

00:34.905 --> 00:37.869
You watch something on YouTube once a week, all right?

00:38.129 --> 00:39.752
How many of you more than once a week?

00:41.875 --> 00:45.780
How many of you never watch it and have no idea what it is?

00:47.462 --> 00:48.243
You need to watch it.

00:48.364 --> 00:50.066
Troy Grambling, all right?

00:50.242 --> 00:53.567
Here, YouTube, it's interesting.

00:53.607 --> 00:56.492
This weekend, what's it called?

00:56.532 --> 01:00.638
VidCon had its convention about YouTube.

01:00.658 --> 01:04.644
And I think last year they had almost 26,000 people show up for it.

01:04.664 --> 01:11.174
In Orlando, Bailey, our daughter, used to go watch all her YouTube people at what was called Playlist.

01:11.755 --> 01:17.384
And I think last year they had 12, 13,000 show up for it.

01:17.985 --> 01:18.866
And if you go,

01:18.946 --> 01:24.332
to YouTube, there's a button that you click that says subscribe.

01:25.033 --> 01:32.442
And subscribe means that you are then going to receive content from that creation maker.

01:32.962 --> 01:40.311
Now, if you pull out that outline you got when you came in, as I was thinking about this series, I thought, well, what does the word subscribe mean?

01:41.412 --> 01:44.976
And I put down the definition from dictionary.com, okay?

01:45.437 --> 01:46.418
Here's what it says.

01:46.978 --> 01:49.881
to pledge as by signing an agreement.

01:50.121 --> 02:00.851
And if you look at the word, you can see the word scribe, which of course means to write, and then sub, which carries the idea of writing your signature at the bottom of a document.

02:01.672 --> 02:08.498
It says to give or pay a sum of money as a contribution, gift or investment.

02:09.199 --> 02:16.466
And then the definition that maybe we're a little more accustomed to, I think it was number six, to agree or assent

02:16.546 --> 02:20.352
And I thought, well, what's the origin of this word?

02:20.632 --> 02:21.754
Subscribe.

02:21.774 --> 02:34.172
And if you go back to the 1540s, it says to give one's consent or to contribute money to in the 1630s, become a regular buyer of a publication in 1711.

02:34.512 --> 02:40.862
Now, when you subscribe to a channel on YouTube, it demands nothing of you.

02:41.683 --> 02:43.225
You don't have to pay any money.

02:43.946 --> 02:46.450
You don't even have to watch their video.

02:46.818 --> 02:50.884
All it means is that you're going to receive their content.

02:51.345 --> 02:58.696
Now I thought that was interesting when I looked at the origin of the word because today the word subscribe means to receive.

02:59.677 --> 03:03.663
But originally the word meant to give, to commit to.

03:03.704 --> 03:13.098
Now we're gonna spend the next seven weeks talking about subscribing and we're gonna talk about subscribe to what?

03:13.178 --> 03:15.922
Well to our ethos here at Potential Church.

03:16.258 --> 03:18.220
the things in which we value.

03:18.661 --> 03:34.521
And it's my hope that at the end of this series, as you think about it in a global sense, but also think about it in a very practical sense, that you'll be able to sign your name, you might say, to those values or to that ethos.

03:35.022 --> 03:41.810
That you'll be able to say, you know what, that's something that I value, that's something that I want to be a part of, that's something I can commit to.

03:42.466 --> 03:45.450
And if you discover, you know what, those aren't things that I value.

03:45.490 --> 04:04.575
They aren't things that are important to me, then that you would be able to find a family or a community in which have the same ethos or values that you have so that you can subscribe so that you can engage, not just receive, but also give part of yourself.

04:05.116 --> 04:10.002
Now, the first value that I want us to talk about is the value of environment.

04:10.434 --> 04:11.976
You've been around potential very long.

04:12.016 --> 04:20.409
We talk about the environment, the environment in a global sense, but also the environment of this room or the environment of the lobby.

04:22.592 --> 04:23.634
Our ethos environment.

04:23.654 --> 04:25.376
Now let me give you my definition, okay?

04:25.857 --> 04:26.838
Here's our definition.

04:27.780 --> 04:34.770
The value of environment is the stewardship of the conditions that surround you and your community.

04:35.458 --> 04:41.046
So it is an old English word stewardship of the conditions that surround you and your community.

04:41.407 --> 04:45.673
It's also an understanding of the impact those conditions have on your success.

04:46.454 --> 04:57.490
So if you think about the environment of the universe, the environment in which we are at this moment, the environment of your family, those conditions, according to scripture, have an impact upon your success.

04:58.071 --> 05:03.218
Now, again, according to the Bible, you and I have an authority

05:04.290 --> 05:07.614
to take control of our environment.

05:07.634 --> 05:10.638
Look what the Scripture says in Genesis chapter 1 verse 26.

05:10.838 --> 05:20.109
It says, then God said, let us make man in our image according to our likeness and let them rule over.

05:20.230 --> 05:21.211
So that's authority.

05:21.671 --> 05:33.586
The fish of the sea, over the birds of the sky, over the cattle, over all the earth and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth.

05:34.082 --> 05:35.124
It's kind of creepy.

05:35.484 --> 05:42.417
Verse 27, God created man in his own image, an image of God he created him, male and female he created them.

05:42.978 --> 05:48.367
God blessed them and God said to them, be fruitful and multiply and fill the earth and subdue it.

05:48.427 --> 05:51.452
New word here, subdue it and rule over it.

05:51.953 --> 05:59.346
Rule over the fish of the sea, over the birds of the sky, over every living thing that moves on the earth.

05:59.906 --> 06:02.730
Several translations translate the word differently.

06:03.351 --> 06:08.059
Some say rule, some say rain, some say have dominion over.

06:08.099 --> 06:10.723
It's the idea of authority.

06:11.484 --> 06:17.975
God said, I created this world and I have given you authority over your environment.

06:19.377 --> 06:22.642
And with authority comes responsibility.

06:23.618 --> 06:28.565
It's not just that you and I have authority, but therefore, because we have authority, we also have responsibility.

06:29.266 --> 06:31.709
We are, and here's the old English word, stewards.

06:32.570 --> 06:36.455
We have stewardship for our environment, a responsibility.

06:36.475 --> 06:42.343
It's kind of like if I were to give you my home and I were to say, I want you to steward it.

06:43.224 --> 06:53.458
I am giving you the authority of my home with that authority of that environment, my house and my yard and whatever else was around.

06:54.306 --> 07:00.855
how responsible you are over what I've given you will have an impact on the relationship you have on me.

07:01.836 --> 07:12.010
In other words, if you don't take any responsibility for it, if you don't keep it up, if you aren't careful about what you allow in, then that's gonna impact.

07:12.050 --> 07:18.038
I'm gonna see that as disloyal, dishonoring, unkind, all those different things.

07:18.319 --> 07:20.882
Well, the same thing is true when it comes to our environment.

07:21.250 --> 07:23.853
God has said, I want you to take authority.

07:23.873 --> 07:25.976
It's not something that happens to you.

07:26.617 --> 07:31.864
You and I are to take dominion over or to steward our environment.

07:31.884 --> 07:36.650
So what I want us to talk about is how do we create an environment that helps us succeed?

07:37.692 --> 07:40.856
Our environment has a lot to do with whether or not we succeed.

07:41.116 --> 07:43.319
And when I use the word success, here's what I mean.

07:43.379 --> 07:48.466
When I'm talking about success, I'm talking about your ability to reach your potential.

07:48.898 --> 08:03.457
to accomplish your destiny, to be everything God has created you to be as a husband, as a wife, as a dad, as a mom, as a teenager, a college student, a business person in the area of your finances, in your health, in your relationships, in your walk with God.

08:03.938 --> 08:05.300
That's what I mean by success.

08:06.121 --> 08:10.467
You're accomplishing the dream or the destiny that God has put inside of your heart.

08:10.747 --> 08:15.954
Well, the environment that you have authority over has an impact

08:16.130 --> 08:19.295
on your ability to accomplish that or to be successful.

08:19.896 --> 08:22.960
Now, I want us to talk about a few of these areas, all right?

08:22.980 --> 08:26.266
And if you pull out the outline you got when you came in, here's the first one.

08:27.547 --> 08:29.871
The people that I do life with.

08:30.873 --> 08:32.215
The people that I do life with.

08:32.435 --> 08:35.239
The people that I allow into my environment.

08:35.980 --> 08:37.463
You have an environment.

08:37.503 --> 08:39.426
Your family has an environment.

08:39.766 --> 08:40.708
And you allow.

08:40.808 --> 08:42.290
You are responsible.

08:42.690 --> 08:48.696
for the people that do life in that environment because they impact us.

08:49.216 --> 08:52.419
It's kind of like, have you ever worn something because you saw somebody else wearing it?

08:53.380 --> 08:54.942
Like, oh, that looks good, I'm gonna wear that.

08:55.182 --> 08:56.723
Have you ever not worn something?

08:58.145 --> 09:01.668
Because you looked somebody like, oh my gosh, that looks terrible.

09:02.208 --> 09:03.189
I'm not gonna wear that.

09:03.450 --> 09:08.735
It's kind of like if you look around and you see, man, it seems like there's so many people with beards.

09:09.876 --> 09:12.338
When I grew up, nobody had a beard, but Santa Claus,

09:12.866 --> 09:14.789
Now it seems like all these people have beards.

09:14.829 --> 09:16.111
Well, how does that happen?

09:16.171 --> 09:18.355
How is it just like poof?

09:18.375 --> 09:22.922
And then, you know, you go a decade where everybody's got, now I'm just jealous because I can't grow one.

09:23.383 --> 09:25.026
I only have to shave every other month.

09:25.146 --> 09:27.590
But how does that happen?

09:27.610 --> 09:30.995
How do, how do a beard, it's because we have impact on one another.

09:31.336 --> 09:32.918
We allow people into our environment.

09:32.939 --> 09:33.800
They have a beard.

09:33.900 --> 09:34.902
It looks cool.

09:35.903 --> 09:40.050
We're like, I'm going to have one of those because I, I desire that.

09:40.226 --> 09:41.247
It impacts us.

09:41.267 --> 09:42.129
Look what the scripture says.

09:42.149 --> 09:43.450
1 Corinthians 15, 33.

09:44.111 --> 09:46.755
It says, do not be, what's the next word?

09:47.836 --> 09:54.746
Okay, when I see that, here's the first thing I always ask myself the question, why does the Bible have to say that?

09:56.007 --> 09:58.971
Why does the Bible have to say, now don't be deceived?

09:59.472 --> 10:01.735
Well, it's because I have a tendency to be deceived.

10:02.556 --> 10:06.802
This is an area in which you and I tend to be naive.

10:07.106 --> 10:09.029
If not, God wouldn't have had to say that.

10:09.069 --> 10:10.531
He wouldn't have to say, now, don't be deceived.

10:10.571 --> 10:11.813
He could have just told us the truth.

10:12.294 --> 10:13.776
But He didn't just give us the truth.

10:14.057 --> 10:17.762
He started it by saying, don't be deceived.

10:18.003 --> 10:20.667
Don't do what you would normally do.

10:21.228 --> 10:22.410
Do not be deceived.

10:22.630 --> 10:27.357
Bad company corrupts or impacts good morals.

10:28.299 --> 10:29.160
What is He saying?

10:30.041 --> 10:35.730
He's saying, you and I have tendency to believe that we're too mature to be impacted by the people around us.

10:36.354 --> 10:48.767
that I can allow people into my environment that may not have the best habits, that may not have the best attitudes, that may not be running after their own success, but it's not gonna impact me.

10:48.827 --> 10:50.469
I'm mature.

10:50.549 --> 10:51.550
I know what my dream is.

10:51.590 --> 10:52.751
I know what my destiny is.

10:52.812 --> 10:54.173
I know what I'm called to do.

10:54.213 --> 10:56.375
I'm bigger than that.

10:56.415 --> 10:57.757
I'm stronger than that.

10:57.797 --> 10:59.118
And what does the scripture say?

10:59.619 --> 11:00.320
Don't be naive.

11:01.781 --> 11:02.642
Don't be deceived.

11:04.034 --> 11:19.497
If you and I want to succeed at our dream and at our destiny, if we want to be successful, he says, then you need to take, I need to take authority over my environment, which is the people that I'm doing life with.

11:19.517 --> 11:28.310
He goes on in 2 Corinthians 6 verse 14, it says, don't develop partnerships with those who are not followers of Jesus Christ.

11:29.051 --> 11:33.618
For what real connection can exist between righteousness and rebellion,

11:34.146 --> 11:36.289
How can light participate in darkness?

11:36.869 --> 11:37.851
Now what's the principle here?

11:38.692 --> 11:44.479
The principle is don't do life with people who are going in different directions.

11:44.499 --> 11:50.807
Because as you follow your dream and they follow their dream, the distance between you is going to only get greater.

11:51.227 --> 12:02.802
And the greater it gets, the more tension there's going to be, the more misunderstanding there's gonna be, the more arguments there's gonna be, the more obstacles you're going to experience in

12:02.882 --> 12:05.025
accomplishing your success or your dream.

12:05.065 --> 12:05.325
Why?

12:05.565 --> 12:06.847
Because I'm way over here.

12:06.987 --> 12:07.988
And you know what I'm doing?

12:08.349 --> 12:10.652
As someone who's doing life with you way over here.

12:11.032 --> 12:11.693
Come on.

12:13.035 --> 12:13.816
Come join me.

12:14.817 --> 12:15.658
Come over here.

12:15.718 --> 12:17.400
Right?

12:17.460 --> 12:19.723
That's what relationally we do.

12:20.264 --> 12:31.538
And in what the Scripture's saying, the principle is, is if you're doing life with somebody who's not going where you're going, they are going to continually be trying to pull you in the opposite direction.

12:31.810 --> 12:34.475
Now the context in which the scripture is written is marriage.

12:35.337 --> 12:42.211
And if you've hung out here very long, you've heard me say on many occasions, I've spoke to those of you who don't believe there's a God.

12:42.371 --> 12:51.730
You're here because your girlfriend, your guy friend, or whoever wanted you to come and just to make them happy, you came.

12:52.258 --> 12:56.263
And the reason I tell you, look, you do not want to marry.

12:56.343 --> 13:04.792
If you don't believe in God, or you don't trust that it's all real, you don't wanna marry a Christ follower, because if you do, you're going to be miserable.

13:06.074 --> 13:13.743
And the reason you're gonna be miserable, because if they are a Christ follower, here's what the Bible teaches, is God the Spirit has taken up residence within their heart.

13:15.044 --> 13:20.210
And God is trying to get them to mature and to grow and to run after Him.

13:20.514 --> 13:22.957
Now, you may be pulling them in the opposite direction.

13:22.977 --> 13:24.660
You may be telling them, oh, you don't need to be...

13:24.680 --> 13:26.883
I mean, why are you so faithful to that church?

13:26.943 --> 13:28.084
Or why are you generous?

13:28.124 --> 13:29.607
Or you don't... You're too busy.

13:29.627 --> 13:31.529
You don't need to be involved in that ministry.

13:31.549 --> 13:32.891
And you may even pull them away.

13:33.832 --> 13:41.383
But I promise you, if they are a Christ follower and they are not following Christ, they're going to be miserable.

13:42.665 --> 13:45.829
They may not be a church on Sunday, but they're going to be miserable.

13:46.109 --> 13:46.690
And guess what?

13:46.790 --> 13:49.554
If they're miserable, so are you going to be.

13:50.498 --> 14:02.519
Now they may not be able to identify why they're miserable, depressed, discouraged, why they're angry, why they have a short temper, but it is impossible as a Christ follower to not follow Christ and be happy.

14:03.241 --> 14:05.024
And eventually, you know what's going to happen?

14:05.084 --> 14:06.226
God's going to grab their heart.

14:06.978 --> 14:12.166
and they're going to surrender to Him and they're going to follow after Him and they're going to actually begin to mature in their faith.

14:12.386 --> 14:15.351
They're going to commit to His house, to His bride.

14:15.651 --> 14:19.357
They're going to engage with their skills and gifts in ministry.

14:19.577 --> 14:28.210
They're even going to grow to the point to where they live a generous life and are actually giving of their resources and what is called an offering.

14:28.270 --> 14:34.199
Your money, your work really hard to give to a place that you don't believe in.

14:34.239 --> 14:34.720
You know what?

14:34.740 --> 14:35.922
You're not going to like that.

14:37.314 --> 14:38.818
And so that's what the Scriptures are saying.

14:38.898 --> 14:39.900
Don't marry them.

14:40.341 --> 14:41.584
Stop dating them.

14:41.925 --> 14:48.220
Get away from them because it is impossible to be happy in the future.

14:48.260 --> 14:51.548
And isn't that part of success?

14:53.332 --> 14:55.858
To have peace, to have joy?

14:56.258 --> 15:02.327
to really be able to engage in every day with a sense of expectation.

15:02.688 --> 15:10.820
And so the writer says, you have an environment, and you and I need to take authority or responsibility for that environment.

15:11.341 --> 15:13.764
Now he lists specifically a few people.

15:14.365 --> 15:17.690
He says that we need to watch out for when it comes to our environment.

15:17.991 --> 15:19.172
First of all, gossips.

15:20.334 --> 15:25.522
He says in Proverbs 1628, a troublemaker plants seeds of strife.

15:26.146 --> 15:29.310
Gossip separates the best of friends.

15:31.053 --> 15:35.559
Now, again, we need to remember.

15:35.579 --> 15:36.260
Remember what he said?

15:36.280 --> 15:37.682
Don't be naive.

15:38.403 --> 15:42.629
The tendency is to believe just because they're a gossip doesn't mean they're going to affect me.

15:42.929 --> 15:44.671
But you know what gossips do?

15:45.212 --> 15:47.816
They create sides.

15:47.836 --> 15:49.458
They create teens.

15:49.858 --> 15:52.642
This person on this side, that person on that side.

15:53.022 --> 15:56.066
And if they're gossiping about one of your friends, you know what else?

15:56.306 --> 15:57.868
They're gossiping about you.

15:59.350 --> 16:02.714
And gossip is negative.

16:02.935 --> 16:05.178
If I come and say, guess what?

16:06.820 --> 16:09.243
Johnny got the promotion.

16:10.204 --> 16:10.965
That's not gossip.

16:10.985 --> 16:12.247
That's a celebration, right?

16:12.968 --> 16:13.869
What's gossip?

16:14.029 --> 16:14.489
Guess what?

16:14.570 --> 16:18.034
Johnny got the promotion because he's sleeping with the boss.

16:19.042 --> 16:19.342
Right?

16:19.423 --> 16:23.188
That's gossip because that's bringing someone else.

16:23.328 --> 16:24.730
So I feel better about myself.

16:24.750 --> 16:26.772
Now we used to say, have you heard?

16:28.575 --> 16:29.456
We don't say that anymore.

16:29.476 --> 16:31.699
We say, have you seen on Instagram?

16:32.160 --> 16:35.104
Have you seen on Facebook?

16:35.124 --> 16:36.465
And what is the scripture saying?

16:36.506 --> 16:37.327
He's saying, you know what?

16:37.387 --> 16:44.196
If you allow gossips into your environment, they're gonna create tension, disunity, and they're gonna separate.

16:44.737 --> 16:45.778
There's gonna be division.

16:46.434 --> 16:49.858
And you know, division makes it really difficult to be successful.

16:51.339 --> 16:57.566
Are companies that are at one another and talking about one another, do they tend to be successful?

16:58.367 --> 16:58.567
No.

16:59.728 --> 17:12.882
If you work at one of those companies where when you see two or three people in the corner talking, you immediately assume they're talking about you because anytime you've been in the corner with two or three people, somebody's talking about somebody, do you enjoy working at those kind of places?

17:13.794 --> 17:17.859
Do you enjoy being in those kind of families, in those kind of environments?

17:17.979 --> 17:19.801
No, it makes it difficult to succeed.

17:20.102 --> 17:22.365
And so God says, hey, I created you to win.

17:22.385 --> 17:27.371
I put inside you everything you need to accomplish the dream that I've put inside of your heart.

17:27.771 --> 17:30.975
And I'm telling you that your environment is important.

17:32.897 --> 17:43.090
And whether it be the streams or the forest and the authority or the responsibility over those environments, the same thing is true when it comes to the people that we allow into our lives.

17:43.842 --> 17:55.955
So he talks about gossip, but then he also talks in the very next verse, verse 29, violent people mislead their companions, leading them down a harmful path, violent.

17:55.976 --> 17:59.740
So don't allow violent people into your environment.

18:00.701 --> 18:09.010
Of course we know that we don't want to allow people who, you know, punch and hurt and create some kind of physical violence.

18:09.730 --> 18:16.136
But I think there's also a violent person that may not be violent to you, but they're violent in their actions.

18:17.077 --> 18:21.702
They throw stuff, they break stuff, they hit stuff.

18:22.963 --> 18:31.051
I remember when I was playing golf in Arkansas years ago, I used to play quite often with a guy that I grew up with, playing baseball.

18:31.431 --> 18:35.595
But when we would play golf, he would get mad and he'd throw his club.

18:36.736 --> 18:38.738
He'd take his club and he'd hit a tree with it.

18:39.394 --> 18:50.291
And I noticed that the more I played with him, the more when I would hit a bad shot, which is just about every time, all right, is my, you know what I'd want to do?

18:50.451 --> 18:51.453
I'd want to throw my club.

18:52.114 --> 18:55.118
And I didn't have enough money to throw my club because then I couldn't get a new one.

18:56.040 --> 19:00.347
I'd want to hit the, you know, and I knew that if I ever did it once, I'd do it over and over again.

19:00.367 --> 19:07.698
I quit playing with him because this scripture says that if I allow people like that into my environment,

19:08.290 --> 19:12.836
Doesn't mean they're horrible meat, it just means that what's it gonna, what does it say it's gonna do?

19:12.876 --> 19:14.779
They're gonna lead me down a harmful path.

19:16.721 --> 19:20.907
They're going to become an obstacle to what God has called and created me to do.

19:21.528 --> 19:25.233
But we're not just violent with our body, we're also violent with our words.

19:27.356 --> 19:35.066
We sometimes allow people into our environment who speak and when they get angry, they use words that hurt.

19:35.086 --> 19:38.130
And I don't mean just angry, I mean the words are just cutting

19:38.594 --> 19:41.658
They're things that just ought not to be ever said.

19:41.698 --> 19:49.807
They're kind of things that even when they apologize, it takes a long time for those wounds to be healed.

19:49.867 --> 19:55.594
And rarely are they healed because before they can be healed, they're cutting at you again.

19:55.674 --> 20:00.700
Deep, hurtful words.

20:02.082 --> 20:05.906
The scripture says, take authority over your environment.

20:07.746 --> 20:09.528
It's not something that's happening to you.

20:09.568 --> 20:10.950
It's something you're allowing in.

20:11.010 --> 20:15.155
And the impact that it's having, he says, remember what he says?

20:15.295 --> 20:16.136
Don't be naive.

20:17.538 --> 20:18.399
Don't be naive.

20:18.819 --> 20:22.103
These things have a way of keeping us from our success.

20:22.564 --> 20:25.728
And then he says greedy people, the wisdom writer, 1527.

20:26.749 --> 20:28.951
Greed brings grief to the whole family.

20:29.552 --> 20:33.397
See, when you and I spend a lot of time around people who are greedy, you know what happens?

20:33.437 --> 20:34.418
We become greedy.

20:35.042 --> 20:54.098
If we spend a lot of time around people who are always talking about how much money they make in their business, they're always talking about the boat that they're going to buy or the house that they just purchased or just all the stuff, the tendency is for us to begin to talk about those very things, to begin to hunger and desire for those very things.

20:54.434 --> 21:02.567
We need to go on that kind of vacation or wear that kind of clothing or have that size house in order to fit in, in order to be part of.

21:02.847 --> 21:04.129
And what does the scripture say?

21:04.370 --> 21:08.556
It says that when we follow those kind of people, it brings grief to the whole family.

21:11.120 --> 21:22.258
And again, if you are grieving, if you are dealing with the frustration of selfishness, the dealing with debt, it makes it very difficult for us to succeed.

21:23.106 --> 21:24.808
I think he says it all in 2 Peter chapter 3.

21:24.828 --> 21:27.752
He says, you already know these things dear friends, so be on guard.

21:27.793 --> 21:32.139
Then you will not be carried away by the heirs of these wicked people.

21:32.159 --> 21:33.721
So I'm not telling you anything you don't know.

21:33.761 --> 21:34.442
You already know.

21:34.702 --> 21:42.673
But what he says is, be on guard, don't be naive, or you'll be carried away and you will lose your footing.

21:42.713 --> 21:44.716
And you know what happens when you lose your footing?

21:46.018 --> 21:46.739
You fall.

21:47.780 --> 21:49.583
How many of you have ever fell in your life?

21:50.644 --> 21:51.826
It's embarrassing.

21:52.226 --> 21:53.788
And it's hurtful, isn't it?

21:54.889 --> 21:58.492
And it slows down your forward progress, doesn't it?

22:00.034 --> 22:06.660
A few years ago, during the Thanksgiving season, we had a competition with one of the guys that used to play NFL football.

22:07.241 --> 22:09.203
And I lost my footing.

22:09.223 --> 22:10.384
Let me show you what happened.

22:14.147 --> 22:15.469
We were having a little contest.

22:16.029 --> 22:17.451
We threw cranberry up there.

22:18.251 --> 22:20.914
And it was a little slicker than I thought that it was.

22:24.514 --> 22:31.121
He was nice enough to help me up, but I couldn't quite get up because the floor was so slick.

22:31.382 --> 22:31.902
Now, you know what?

22:32.002 --> 22:33.904
In slow motion, as I was falling, you know what?

22:33.924 --> 22:36.627
I thought all the way to the ground, I can catch myself.

22:36.647 --> 22:38.610
I can regain my balance.

22:39.230 --> 22:40.412
And isn't that what we tend to do?

22:41.072 --> 22:41.232
Right?

22:41.272 --> 22:44.476
We tend to think, I'm mature enough.

22:44.496 --> 22:45.337
I'm strong enough.

22:45.357 --> 22:46.839
I'm not going to fall.

22:48.260 --> 22:53.586
That person is not going to keep me from my destiny, but that's not what the Scripture says.

22:54.850 --> 22:55.771
Be a good steward.

22:57.173 --> 23:01.198
Take authority over your environment, the people you allow in.

23:01.558 --> 23:04.201
Secondly, the attitudes that I allow.

23:04.261 --> 23:07.986
What kind of attitude do you allow yourself to have?

23:08.807 --> 23:11.670
It's so easy to focus on the wrong things, wouldn't you say?

23:11.711 --> 23:20.701
The scripture says in Philippians two, it says you must have the same attitude that Christ Jesus had, which in the next verses is humility.

23:20.842 --> 23:24.466
And then he says in verse 14, do everything without

23:24.962 --> 23:27.987
Complaining and arguing, can I have an amen?

23:29.469 --> 23:29.689
Right?

23:29.769 --> 23:35.639
I mean, you must have the same attitude that Christ Jesus had, do everything without complaining and arguing.

23:36.039 --> 23:36.760
You know what?

23:36.800 --> 23:37.802
We're gonna read that together.

23:38.663 --> 23:45.394
I think it would be, because some of you screwed that up on your way to church today, okay?

23:45.414 --> 23:49.660
Some of you screwed it up sitting in that chair that you're sitting in or watching on television.

23:49.720 --> 23:50.862
So here we go, we're gonna read it together.

23:52.565 --> 23:53.426
Ah, take a deep breath.

23:54.946 --> 23:59.452
You must have the same attitude that Christ Jesus had.

23:59.993 --> 24:07.022
Do you have somebody in mind as you were reading that?

24:07.042 --> 24:09.985
Just know this, they had you in mind at the same time, okay?

24:11.788 --> 24:22.802
He tells us what, our attitude has impact and that our attitude, the attitude we invite into our environment is important.

24:23.394 --> 24:27.721
Because the attitude we have is expressed in the words that we say.

24:27.761 --> 24:31.848
And the Scripture teaches us that our words have life and they have death.

24:32.469 --> 24:34.773
Look at what James says in chapter 3 verse 2.

24:34.813 --> 24:38.079
He says, indeed, we all make many mistakes.

24:38.639 --> 24:41.284
For if we could control our tongues, what does he mean?

24:41.484 --> 24:42.546
Our words

24:42.882 --> 24:46.246
We would be perfect and could also control ourselves in every other way.

24:46.546 --> 24:47.287
What is he saying?

24:47.547 --> 24:53.313
He's saying that if I can determine my words, my words direct my life.

24:54.635 --> 24:58.179
If I want to succeed, then I need to talk toward success.

24:59.640 --> 25:03.725
And what I say is gonna come out of my heart, it's gonna come out of my attitude.

25:04.526 --> 25:12.274
And if my attitude is negative and my attitude is discouraged and my attitude is one of defeat, then where's my life gonna go according to scripture?

25:12.610 --> 25:13.712
It's going to go to defeat.

25:13.892 --> 25:17.157
See, I'm not speaking defeat because I'm failing.

25:17.278 --> 25:22.406
I'm failing according to the scripture because I'm speaking defeat because he goes on.

25:22.426 --> 25:22.967
Look what he says.

25:23.007 --> 25:28.155
He says, we can make a large horse go whatever way we want with a small bit in its mouth.

25:28.596 --> 25:33.945
Small rudder makes a huge ship turn wherever the pilot chooses to go, even though the winds are strong.

25:33.965 --> 25:34.566
What does that mean?

25:34.946 --> 25:39.634
The wind is coming in in opposition of the direction the ship wants to go.

25:39.842 --> 25:47.402
But that little tiny rudder can overcome the wind and go in whatever direction the pilot wants it to go.

25:47.443 --> 25:48.886
So think about your life.

25:49.649 --> 25:54.642
You may look around, you may say, there's lots of wind in opposition to my success.

25:54.978 --> 25:56.500
I didn't go to the right school.

25:56.580 --> 25:57.802
I don't have the right job.

25:57.862 --> 25:59.064
I didn't get the right degree.

25:59.444 --> 26:00.646
I don't have the right money.

26:01.046 --> 26:02.008
All of these different things.

26:02.048 --> 26:02.789
What is he saying?

26:03.049 --> 26:11.300
Is it when you and I invite the right attitudes into our life, there is no wind of opposition that can keep us from our success.

26:12.182 --> 26:14.925
That's how important our attitudes are.

26:14.986 --> 26:18.851
That's how important our environment is.

26:20.493 --> 26:21.334
It's so easy.

26:21.374 --> 26:24.018
I've been working on this.

26:24.674 --> 26:26.178
asking myself these questions.

26:26.859 --> 26:28.523
So many times when someone says, well, how do you feel?

26:29.205 --> 26:30.307
How do you answer that question?

26:30.929 --> 26:31.711
How was your day?

26:31.871 --> 26:33.054
How do you answer that question?

26:33.776 --> 26:35.440
What kind of day will it be?

26:35.480 --> 26:38.487
I mean, do you get up in the morning when you know it's going to be a busy day?

26:38.788 --> 26:41.394
And are you prophesying success or defeat?

26:42.370 --> 26:54.849
Do you talk about how busy you're going to be and how tired you're going to be and what a pain that that supervisor is and how horrible the traffic is and how the kids are never ready and just all of these things.

26:54.869 --> 27:00.778
You know what the Scripture says when you invite those words into your environment, those words are directing your life.

27:03.763 --> 27:08.530
And what if you were and I were to invite the other type of words into our life?

27:09.794 --> 27:16.144
What if we were to speak not discouragement and defeat, but we were to speak victory?

27:17.366 --> 27:25.760
What if we were to get up each day and say, I'm going to steer my life according to Scripture by inviting into my environment that I have control over?

27:25.800 --> 27:29.286
You have authority over.

27:29.326 --> 27:32.050
God gave it to you in Genesis chapter 1.

27:33.058 --> 27:35.501
Your boss doesn't have authority over your attitude.

27:35.541 --> 27:37.023
Your spouse doesn't have authority.

27:37.063 --> 27:40.448
Your kids, your parents, your neighbor, the president.

27:40.488 --> 27:43.913
Nobody has authority over your attitude except for you.

27:43.973 --> 27:46.216
God said, take dominion.

27:46.516 --> 27:48.078
Have a rule.

27:48.399 --> 27:51.202
Be a steward of your environment.

27:52.043 --> 27:55.909
And sometimes I think we look around and we say, man, why can't I seem to succeed?

27:55.949 --> 27:59.954
And it's because you have a polluted environment.

28:01.538 --> 28:06.604
You have attitudes that are expressed in words that are just obstacles.

28:07.925 --> 28:14.592
Ephesians 4 says, let the Spirit, the Holy Spirit renew your thoughts and attitudes.

28:15.634 --> 28:18.637
Don't use foul or abusive language.

28:19.218 --> 28:26.866
You know, I think sometimes we allow our circumstances to be an excuse for our words.

28:27.810 --> 28:29.733
And you think about it.

28:29.753 --> 28:35.022
Sometimes we allow pain if you hurt yourself.

28:35.042 --> 28:37.366
And then you use some very colorful words.

28:38.669 --> 28:40.071
What do people normally do?

28:40.131 --> 28:46.903
We normally very quickly excuse our language with, that's just, that's not me.

28:48.265 --> 28:49.086
I'm just hurting.

28:49.106 --> 28:51.250
That hurt.

28:52.578 --> 28:54.180
Well, again, you know what the Bible says?

28:54.221 --> 29:01.432
The Bible says that there are no words spoken from our mouth that haven't taken residence within our heart.

29:01.452 --> 29:02.513
See, that's who you are.

29:02.553 --> 29:07.241
It's just that you have been strong enough to hide who you are.

29:07.261 --> 29:15.513
And when pain or frustration or difficulty has come into your life, who you lose that strength.

29:15.534 --> 29:19.279
And so who you and I really are then comes out.

29:19.299 --> 29:21.042
Now, I know some of you arguing with me right now.

29:22.466 --> 29:33.379
because you're sitting next to somebody who heard words come out of your mouth even on the way to this gathering that you would declare are not who you are.

29:35.261 --> 29:49.778
And my challenge to you is not to argue with me, but rather to take the expression of those words as an opportunity to come to the realization that that might be the reason you have so much struggle in succeeding.

29:51.426 --> 30:00.361
that that might be the obstacle, that God is used pain to reveal to us who we really are, what our environment really is.

30:00.622 --> 30:09.096
It's like the stream that's polluted way at the bottom, but on the top they put in some chemicals that make it look like it's good, but when you drink it, you get sick.

30:10.098 --> 30:12.262
Well, you and I often do that in our own lives.

30:12.663 --> 30:14.706
We hide who we really are.

30:15.778 --> 30:23.730
And as a result, we never actually succeed at the dream or destiny that we have because we just won't be honest enough to say, you know what?

30:24.231 --> 30:26.675
I have allowed into my environment pollution.

30:27.877 --> 30:32.904
I have allowed into my environment those things that make it more difficult for me to succeed.

30:34.046 --> 30:36.870
Just don't let foul or abusive language.

30:37.892 --> 30:41.938
He says, let everything you say be good and helpful.

30:42.338 --> 30:46.143
so that your words will be an encouragement to those who hear them.

30:47.264 --> 30:50.108
Now, I want you to see numbers 14.

30:50.368 --> 30:54.854
If you hear last weekend, we talked a little bit about how God's people went into the promised land.

30:54.874 --> 30:55.655
Remember the story.

30:56.175 --> 30:57.677
Moses went and got them in Egypt.

30:58.559 --> 31:00.080
He took them to the Jordan River.

31:01.042 --> 31:03.705
Then he sent 12 spies to go into the promised land.

31:03.725 --> 31:08.952
The promised land represents in the scripture success, destiny, purpose.

31:08.972 --> 31:10.834
These 12 spies went in.

31:11.042 --> 31:12.064
They came back.

31:12.384 --> 31:14.647
Ten said, we cannot do this.

31:14.888 --> 31:16.490
There are giants in the land.

31:16.851 --> 31:19.194
Two of them said, we can do it.

31:19.735 --> 31:22.199
One of them was Joshua, the other was Caleb.

31:22.299 --> 31:24.963
Now look what the scripture says in verse 24.

31:25.363 --> 31:29.970
But my servant Caleb has a different, what's the next word?

31:31.042 --> 31:32.605
A different attitude than the others have.

31:32.665 --> 31:34.187
He has remained loyal to me.

31:34.448 --> 31:38.775
So because of his attitude, I will bring him into the land he explored.

31:39.156 --> 31:42.662
His descendants will possess their full share of that land.

31:43.263 --> 31:46.248
Caleb said, I want that mountain.

31:46.769 --> 31:51.657
When the 10 came back and said, we can't, Caleb saw the same giants.

31:51.678 --> 31:53.080
He saw the same obstacles.

31:53.100 --> 31:54.502
He saw the same struggles.

31:55.444 --> 31:56.626
But Caleb said,

31:57.218 --> 31:59.421
God has promised us that land.

31:59.681 --> 32:05.209
God is faithful to keep His promises, and I am not going to surrender to fear.

32:05.589 --> 32:09.394
Instead, let's go get what God said was ours.

32:09.755 --> 32:13.280
I will live my destiny, and I will experience my purpose.

32:13.300 --> 32:17.886
He did not allow into His environment a negative attitude.

32:17.906 --> 32:18.927
And what the Scripture says?

32:19.408 --> 32:23.834
You know what happened to the other 10, and everybody else that was about that age?

32:24.335 --> 32:25.656
They wondered for 40 years.

32:25.917 --> 32:26.898
They never

32:27.042 --> 32:29.364
they were never as successful as they could have been.

32:29.404 --> 32:32.387
They saw success, but they never entered into it.

32:32.707 --> 32:34.309
They never lived their destiny.

32:34.389 --> 32:36.051
They never accomplished their purpose.

32:36.231 --> 32:44.799
You don't have frustrating that is to see what you could have been, to see the dream and the destiny to watch others walk into what was yours.

32:45.119 --> 32:56.210
They never experienced, but Caleb, who saw the same giants who experienced the same fear, but because of his attitude, the scripture says he went in to the promised land.

32:57.026 --> 32:58.768
He experienced his destiny.

33:02.053 --> 33:03.915
You realize how important your environment is?

33:06.699 --> 33:15.651
And how pollution allowed into our life, whether it be the people that we're doing life with or the attitudes.

33:15.871 --> 33:23.922
And then the last thing I'd share with you is to create this environment for success, it's dependent upon the beauty I integrate.

33:25.058 --> 33:26.359
the beauty I integrate.

33:26.379 --> 33:30.883
We're created with a hunger or a desire, a longing for beauty.

33:32.525 --> 33:35.147
We move towards beauty.

33:36.929 --> 33:39.832
We tend to be inspired by beauty.

33:40.152 --> 33:41.453
And that's not by accident.

33:41.553 --> 33:43.075
God created us that way.

33:44.036 --> 33:51.242
Ecclesiastes chapter three verse 11 says, God has made everything beautiful for its own time.

33:52.464 --> 33:55.026
If you've ever read the first chapter of Genesis,

33:55.586 --> 33:58.331
God creates the world in the first six days.

33:58.771 --> 34:05.242
And after each day's creation, he steps back and he says, it is what?

34:05.302 --> 34:05.783
Anybody know?

34:06.484 --> 34:06.765
Good.

34:06.985 --> 34:07.746
He says it is good.

34:08.087 --> 34:10.731
Now that's a Hebrew word, the Old Testament's written in Hebrew.

34:11.052 --> 34:14.558
That same Hebrew word could be translated as beautiful.

34:15.620 --> 34:21.810
You could just as honestly translate that and God said it is beautiful.

34:22.050 --> 34:25.215
Now the translation, the voice translates it that way.

34:25.255 --> 34:26.156
Let me read it to you.

34:26.877 --> 34:27.718
It's in your outline.

34:27.758 --> 34:34.048
Then God surveyed everything that he had made, savoring its beauty and appreciating its goodness.

34:35.109 --> 34:36.571
Evening gave way to mourning.

34:36.932 --> 34:38.614
That was day six.

34:39.696 --> 34:43.101
So the first five days, God steps back and he says, it is beautiful.

34:43.221 --> 34:47.808
On the sixth day, God steps back and he says, it is very beautiful.

34:48.148 --> 34:50.272
Now there's a difference between pretty and beautiful.

34:51.173 --> 34:51.954
Beautiful.

34:52.066 --> 34:54.829
is good and it is true.

34:55.470 --> 34:59.335
It's kind of like if you think about the model on the front of the Glamour magazine.

35:00.937 --> 35:04.682
She may be pretty, but she's not beautiful.

35:04.742 --> 35:07.665
And the reason is because beauty is true.

35:07.705 --> 35:12.071
That model didn't look like that when she got up that morning.

35:13.072 --> 35:14.834
They've done a little work on that picture.

35:15.266 --> 35:17.411
Maybe even a little work on her, all right?

35:17.632 --> 35:20.499
Or him, depending on what kind of magazine that it is.

35:20.579 --> 35:21.682
Doesn't mean that it's bad.

35:21.722 --> 35:24.829
It's pretty, but it's not deeper than that.

35:26.273 --> 35:27.836
It's not beautiful.

35:27.876 --> 35:28.638
It's like the cross.

35:28.698 --> 35:33.490
The cross is not pretty, but it is beautiful because it is true.

35:33.954 --> 35:38.001
Now, I want us to look at this beauty that we need to invite into our environment.

35:38.081 --> 35:38.362
Why?

35:38.602 --> 35:40.646
Because it is going to inspire.

35:40.927 --> 35:42.349
It's going to impassion.

35:42.650 --> 35:43.792
It's going to bring peace.

35:43.892 --> 35:45.034
It's going to bring joy.

35:45.335 --> 35:50.404
And here's going to be my question is how intentional have you been about bringing beauty into your environment?

35:51.285 --> 35:58.258
Or have you been so busy going from point A to point B running from here to there that you really haven't thought about your environment?

35:59.330 --> 36:02.134
The gates open and anybody that wants to come in comes in.

36:02.435 --> 36:04.618
And you really haven't thought about your attitude.

36:04.658 --> 36:06.081
If you're frustrated, you show it.

36:06.121 --> 36:07.443
If you're mad, you show it.

36:08.164 --> 36:09.827
If you've been mistreated, you yell.

36:10.067 --> 36:14.594
And you sure hadn't spent the time to think about, how do I invite beauty into my environment?

36:16.217 --> 36:19.101
Into my family, into my world.

36:19.762 --> 36:21.044
Well, let's think about it.

36:21.064 --> 36:24.690
There is beauty, first of all, in creation, which is what we see.

36:25.378 --> 36:29.604
Psalms 19 says, the heaven declare the glory of God.

36:29.965 --> 36:33.290
The sky displays His handiwork day after day.

36:33.350 --> 36:36.434
It speaks out night after night.

36:36.594 --> 36:38.738
It reveals His greatness.

36:40.280 --> 36:40.460
Right?

36:40.480 --> 36:44.466
I mean, even the atheist looks at a sunset and says, that's beautiful.

36:46.114 --> 36:52.342
There's something about a sunset or a sunrise or something about the stars in the sky at night.

36:52.382 --> 37:04.799
There's something about watching the clouds float by or the mountains in the background or one single flower springing up in the middle of a big chunk of asphalt.

37:04.819 --> 37:06.521
Something beautiful about that.

37:06.802 --> 37:16.114
And when you and I take the time to invite that beauty into our environment, it has a way of inspiring.

37:16.898 --> 37:18.680
It has a way of bringing peace.

37:19.621 --> 37:31.935
And whether it's flowers or whether it's what gifts that God's given artists to take color and shape and put them together in such a way that when you look at that art, it inspires you.

37:32.016 --> 37:33.697
It quiets your heart.

37:33.858 --> 37:37.001
It slows your anxiety.

37:37.522 --> 37:40.345
It reminds you that there's something greater.

37:40.565 --> 37:44.530
There's something more than just the next email on your phone.

37:47.170 --> 37:53.099
So if we're going to be successful in the dream that's in our heart, then we have to be intentional about our environment.

37:53.339 --> 37:58.427
We have to be intentional about inviting this kind of beauty into that environment.

37:58.447 --> 37:59.709
And my question is, have you?

38:01.071 --> 38:05.378
What kind of beauty have you invited into your environment this week?

38:05.398 --> 38:07.882
What kind of pictures do you have on the wall?

38:07.922 --> 38:15.794
What kind of great thing about technology is you can even go and look at some of the world's finest art, or where have you gone to?

38:16.834 --> 38:36.573
I mean, if you stepped outside at night and just looked at the stars, or looked at that flower, springing up through the concrete, or the beauty and God's creation of nature, or this animal, or some fine piece of art at some museum, or have you just been too busy?

38:38.095 --> 38:40.157
And your environment hasn't had any of those things.

38:40.457 --> 38:45.682
But not only is there beauty in creation and what we see, but there's also beauty in music, what we hear.

38:46.498 --> 38:49.661
Psalm 150 says, praise him for his mighty works.

38:50.002 --> 38:51.964
Praise his unequaled greatness.

38:52.445 --> 38:54.487
Praise him with a blast of the ram's horn.

38:54.527 --> 38:56.129
Praise him with the lyre and heart.

38:56.149 --> 38:58.731
Praise him with the tambourine and with dancing.

38:58.772 --> 39:00.213
Praise him with strings and flutes.

39:00.293 --> 39:01.815
Praise him with a clash of cymbals.

39:02.155 --> 39:04.298
Praise him with loud clanging cymbals.

39:04.358 --> 39:07.041
Let everything that breathes sing praises to the Lord.

39:07.401 --> 39:08.502
Praise the Lord.

39:09.403 --> 39:15.570
Music, again, has a way of creating emotion and feelings.

39:16.194 --> 39:16.835
in our lives.

39:19.018 --> 39:21.162
Have you heard, you know, Beethoven for Babies?

39:22.544 --> 39:27.091
It's supposed to impact their minds and they're supposed to help them be better learners.

39:27.111 --> 39:39.730
There's actually now music therapy for certain illnesses, or they've discovered that certain types of music help the body heal itself in more effectively and in quicker ways.

39:41.058 --> 39:46.737
I mean, I don't play an instrument I can't sing, and yet I am moved by music.

39:48.503 --> 39:51.794
I'm not talking about turning on the radio and vegging out.

39:52.642 --> 39:55.586
I'm not talking about escaping from your problems.

39:55.987 --> 39:59.973
I'm not talking about numbing yourself to what's going on in your environment.

40:00.013 --> 40:17.298
No, no, I'm talking about the intentionality of bringing into your environment, bringing into your world music, the beauty of the way that it fits together and the emotion that you experience, the passion

40:18.818 --> 40:26.229
that just comes within your heart or the desire, the call to be greater, to do more.

40:28.012 --> 40:40.731
One of the channels I listen to on YouTube has a lot of different playlists and some of them are, you know, here's music to be productive and here's music to study and here's music to relax and here's music to be creative.

40:42.995 --> 40:44.056
Do you slow down enough?

40:44.817 --> 40:47.922
I don't mean music in the background to cover up

40:48.290 --> 40:54.919
you know, the dogs or the kids or your other workmates, or to make you forget about working out.

40:54.979 --> 41:03.731
I'm talking about, have you intentionally brought music, the beauty to inspire you to bring peace?

41:04.391 --> 41:09.098
Remember the story in the Old Testament of Saul who was king and David who played the harp?

41:10.359 --> 41:18.290
And the scripture says that Saul would invite David to come and play his harp because it would bring peace to his heart.

41:20.706 --> 41:22.028
Maybe there's something to that.

41:22.689 --> 41:24.151
And maybe you've just been too busy.

41:26.054 --> 41:30.800
Maybe your environment lacks the beauty that God created to help you succeed.

41:32.543 --> 41:34.185
And you just haven't gotten around to it.

41:35.487 --> 41:38.311
And then there is the beauty of love.

41:39.112 --> 41:40.434
And love is what we feel.

41:41.122 --> 41:42.804
Love is patient and kind.

41:42.904 --> 41:45.566
Love is not jealous or boastful or proud or rude.

41:45.887 --> 41:47.528
It does not demand its own way.

41:47.588 --> 41:50.931
It is not irritable and it keeps no record of being wrong.

41:51.532 --> 41:55.976
It does not rejoice about injustice but rejoices whenever truth wins out.

41:56.317 --> 41:57.478
Love never gives up.

41:57.558 --> 42:03.163
It never loses faith and it's always hopeful and endures through every circumstance.

42:03.483 --> 42:07.467
Have you invited the beauty of love into your environment?

42:07.948 --> 42:08.829
I mean, think about it.

42:09.449 --> 42:10.290
Kindness.

42:11.362 --> 42:17.454
Remember when someone showed you kindness and have you intentionally, again, brought that beauty into your environment.

42:17.474 --> 42:18.897
Maybe it's a note that they wrote.

42:19.197 --> 42:21.201
Maybe it's a gift that they gave you.

42:21.622 --> 42:29.998
Maybe it's an email that they sent, but it's something that's there in front of you to remind you so that you can experience the beauty of their kindness.

42:30.679 --> 42:34.066
What they did, they had no reason to do other than love.

42:34.594 --> 42:41.723
And every time you think about what they did and the amount of time that it took for them to do that or the way in which they express that, what does it do?

42:41.743 --> 42:42.925
It inspires you.

42:42.945 --> 42:45.848
It brings joy to your heart.

42:45.929 --> 42:49.874
It gives you a confidence in what God's created once again.

42:49.934 --> 42:50.975
Or maybe it's forgiveness.

42:53.098 --> 42:54.139
Maybe you did something.

42:54.800 --> 42:55.861
Maybe it was intentionally.

42:55.901 --> 42:56.662
Maybe it wasn't.

42:56.702 --> 42:57.904
But here's one thing we all know.

42:58.304 --> 42:59.506
It hurt them.

43:00.450 --> 43:02.812
And the hurt that they felt was real.

43:03.072 --> 43:08.597
But rather than trying to get revenge upon you or to get you back, they forgave you.

43:08.617 --> 43:15.703
And in their forgiveness, they sent you a gift or they sent you a note or they left a voicemail or something.

43:15.743 --> 43:22.049
And every time you see that gift, every time you read that note, you are brought to a higher point.

43:22.089 --> 43:22.329
Why?

43:22.589 --> 43:24.591
Because you see the beauty of their love.

43:24.811 --> 43:30.436
You see the beauty of their willingness to give to you an experience that you don't deserve.

43:30.416 --> 43:34.101
Have you invited that in?

43:36.564 --> 43:46.897
You know, one of the things this year that I'm thinking about is a picture of maybe your spouse or a child, right?

43:47.137 --> 43:50.922
Again, even an atheist sees a picture of a baby and smiles.

43:51.783 --> 43:52.644
They don't know why.

43:52.705 --> 43:54.146
As a Christ follower, you know why.

43:54.206 --> 44:00.114
The Bible says that we are made in God's image, that all things were made by Him for Him and through Him.

44:01.250 --> 44:11.643
But every time you look at that child, your love that you feel for that child, it doesn't matter what that child came into the world with.

44:11.703 --> 44:23.779
The world may look at that child and may see it as something that's not beautiful, some kind of disease or difficulty.

44:23.819 --> 44:29.266
I know Steph's sister has a cade was born with Down syndrome.

44:29.922 --> 44:40.882
It's amazing that every time someone looks at a picture of Cade or they see Cade or they're told something that Cade did, there's always a smile that comes to their face.

44:41.182 --> 44:50.900
And you can see within their eyes that they are remembering and experiencing the love that he so freely gives every time that you're around him.

44:52.142 --> 44:54.546
Every time he's invited into that environment,

44:54.786 --> 44:57.369
whether it be through a picture or in some other way.

44:57.650 --> 44:58.430
You know what he brings?

44:58.611 --> 44:59.832
He brings a piece.

45:01.254 --> 45:04.498
He brings a sense that there is more to life.

45:06.260 --> 45:19.356
As I said, one of the things that we've done this year is these little mugs, these Temple Centurion, you know, anybody that gives $99, we send one of these mugs to.

45:19.777 --> 45:20.517
It's not a gift.

45:21.759 --> 45:24.242
It's not a thank you even.

45:24.962 --> 45:26.504
It's a, it's a, it's a remembrance.

45:26.524 --> 45:28.587
It's something to bring into your environment.

45:29.107 --> 45:35.736
I, I, I, step and I have one of these and every time I go to get coffee and that's a lot, I'm always, I'm looking for this mug.

45:36.356 --> 45:39.861
And it's not because it's pretty to look at, although it's pretty to look at.

45:40.181 --> 45:47.651
The reason I always want this mug is because every time I take a drink, I am reminded of what it represents.

45:48.231 --> 45:53.458
I talked with one of the gentlemen that we partner with, uh, we're a part of a,

45:53.570 --> 46:00.177
partnership or a network with some pastors and business leaders from some of the largest churches in the world.

46:00.277 --> 46:02.840
And we hosted that a few years ago, some of you might remember.

46:03.241 --> 46:12.110
We was telling me that we were given by the Kurds in Northern Iraq a large piece of land.

46:13.652 --> 46:22.642
And we have begun to build a clinic, a school, and the largest Christian church in Iraq

46:23.362 --> 46:24.604
on that piece of property.

46:25.586 --> 46:46.962
And so every time I take a drink of coffee from this cup, I am reminded, I am reminded about the impact that our relationship, our generosity is having on kids that I may never meet in an area that is, I can't imagine the challenge they face.

46:47.650 --> 46:52.345
If you go to northern Iraq, the cities there are quite nice, but these are the refuge camps.

46:52.365 --> 47:01.074
This clinic and this school and this church are going to minister to the refugees who flee away from ISIS.

47:01.346 --> 47:03.468
fearful of losing their life.

47:03.608 --> 47:08.512
Many of them are children whose mom and dads have lost their life, literally lost their head.

47:08.853 --> 47:13.076
And every time I look at this cup, I am reminded that I didn't just not do anything.

47:13.176 --> 47:14.758
I've done something about that.

47:15.058 --> 47:19.682
That love has called me to something greater, to something higher.

47:19.742 --> 47:27.629
And when I look, I am reminded that the beauty of that love and that I can be a part of something, I can do something.

47:27.649 --> 47:31.332
It gives me a peace and at the same time it calls me

47:31.312 --> 47:34.074
took something greater, it calls me to my potential.

47:35.215 --> 47:52.631
He also told me that they had a recent heat wave there in Iraq, in the area in which we're ministering, and several thousand people died because of the heat, and they're on these refugee camps and children and older people, they died.

47:53.352 --> 48:00.658
And so what we did is we were able to purchase some, not air conditioners, but these air movers that put water into the air.

48:01.122 --> 48:07.248
And as a result, in these dwellings, it lowers the temperature by 10 degrees.

48:08.529 --> 48:14.615
And he said that we were able to rescue or to help 48,200 families.

48:15.896 --> 48:16.237
All right?

48:16.957 --> 48:22.963
Now, that's inspiring to me.

48:24.505 --> 48:25.626
That's impassioned.

48:25.666 --> 48:27.067
That brings passion to me.

48:28.969 --> 48:29.970
That's beautiful.

48:31.554 --> 48:35.279
that people like you and me who may never go there.

48:36.321 --> 48:54.768
I mean, may never meet those people, but because of love, the beauty of love, we have sacrificed of our own things that we might have needed or desired so that they could experience life, so that they could have a church, so that they could go to a clinic.

48:56.310 --> 48:58.313
Have you intentionally brought those things into your life?

49:00.296 --> 49:01.458
Into your environment?

49:02.402 --> 49:04.325
Again, it's so easy to get busy, isn't it?

49:05.066 --> 49:07.049
It's so easy to run from here and there.

49:07.089 --> 49:10.274
It's so easy to try to do so many things in order to succeed.

49:10.595 --> 49:18.588
When God has said, I want you to take authority over your environment so that you can succeed.

49:20.030 --> 49:26.019
Look at the last verse, Psalm 27.4, what does an environment of success look like?

49:27.361 --> 49:30.226
The psalmist says, I am pleading with the eternal for this one thing.

49:30.690 --> 49:42.365
My soul's desire to live with Him all the days of my life in the shadow of His temple, to behold His beauty and to ponder His ways in the company of His people.

49:42.405 --> 49:43.006
What does that mean?

49:43.366 --> 49:47.391
It means to be in right relationship with God and with people.

49:48.953 --> 49:54.561
That's what true success is, right relationship with God and with people.

49:54.961 --> 49:57.184
What people am I bringing into my environment?

49:57.244 --> 49:58.866
What kind of attitude?

49:59.970 --> 50:03.475
Am I allowing into my environment and what kind of beauty?

50:05.718 --> 50:10.324
One last thing, you know, earlier they came out here and they invited you to the baptism.

50:12.067 --> 50:12.587
You know why?

50:12.607 --> 50:16.533
Oh, of course, if you're here and you've not been obedient, you need to.

50:17.734 --> 50:20.338
But even if you have, you know why you need to be there?

50:22.114 --> 50:25.198
not just for the ability to do life with one another.

50:25.519 --> 50:25.779
Why?

50:25.839 --> 50:29.724
It's because every time somebody goes into that water, what is that a picture of?

50:29.964 --> 50:32.147
That is a picture of a transformed life.

50:32.468 --> 50:38.115
That is a picture of someone who is going to spend eternity separated from God, who is now going to spend eternity with God.

50:38.155 --> 50:44.023
It's a picture of someone who's life, who's family, whose future is completely transformed.

50:44.043 --> 50:44.724
Do you know what that is?

50:45.044 --> 50:46.226
It's beautiful.

50:47.490 --> 50:54.921
It's beautiful to believe that this all-powerful God would step into this world and transform a life that way.

50:55.302 --> 50:57.124
And we invite you to be there.

50:57.164 --> 50:57.585
Why?

50:58.006 --> 51:00.189
So you can bring that beauty into your life.

51:01.892 --> 51:02.833
Don't be too busy.

51:04.856 --> 51:05.878
Don't be unaware.

51:06.919 --> 51:07.941
Don't be naive.

51:09.723 --> 51:11.306
You were created to succeed.

51:12.888 --> 51:16.914
Every one of us, none of us have to fail.

51:18.786 --> 51:29.599
But our environment, what we value here at potential, that ethos, who, what kind of attitude and how much beauty.

51:29.639 --> 51:31.261
Father, I thank you.

51:31.281 --> 51:48.402
I thank you that you have given us the responsibility and the authority for our environment, for the people that we allow open up the door to, for the attitudes,

51:49.378 --> 51:54.869
that we express and for the beauty that we're intentional to bring in.

51:56.472 --> 52:05.068
I pray that we should, that we shall succeed in Jesus' name.

52:05.088 --> 52:05.409
Amen.

52:06.351 --> 52:08.114
Thank you guys so much for being here.

